<div id="review_1766230900" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1766230900" />
    <a title="James Violand" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6308377-james-violand"><img alt="James Violand" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1388703262p2/6308377.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1766230900?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="James Violand" class="user" itemprop="url" name="James Violand" href="/user/show/6308377-james-violand">James Violand</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9008650086" href="/book/show/15705339-the-assemblies-of-al-hariri">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">everyone.</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6308377-james-violand?shelf=own">own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1766230900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9814294767206514965">Remote times knew truths that modernity has forgotten. The book is flushed with wisdom though this particular container is difficult to handle. The translation curves pitches of wisdom into near misses and leads to confusion. (How can rubbing two sticks together ever &quot;spark&quot; a fire?) And yet other pearls are perfect: &quot;Our age selects only the fool for its favours.&quot; <br/>The mechanism of the assemblies is Abu Zayd, a roguish, thieving and endearing character who employs his tongue to earn a living. Ea</span>
  <span id="freeText9814294767206514965" style="display:none">Remote times knew truths that modernity has forgotten. The book is flushed with wisdom though this particular container is difficult to handle. The translation curves pitches of wisdom into near misses and leads to confusion. (How can rubbing two sticks together ever "spark" a fire?) And yet other pearls are perfect: "Our age selects only the fool for its favours." <br />The mechanism of the assemblies is Abu Zayd, a roguish, thieving and endearing character who employs his tongue to earn a living. Each chapter is a group setting where Abu counterfeits virtue in order to take money from the gullible. <br />The lessons learned could lead to a better life.<br />If I could find a better translation, I would sell other books to acquire it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9814294767206514965" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


